<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Crash driven design.  Design your software such that it can recover from a crash to a known state and continue.  Make life so much simpler.  Shutdown is just a matter of power off.  Startup always does a recovery before starting.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=200></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3357234 href="vote?for=3357234&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%67%32%63%4c%74%32%37%4d%7a%6e"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3357234></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=nialo">nialo</a> 52 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3357234">link</a></span></div><br>
